cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.SI, cs.CY

This paper discusses a privacy-enhancing framework for IPTV recommender services, which involves the use of trust mechanisms and secure multiparty computation protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases). The paper also involves the use of proximity metrics and neighborhood formation, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
